{
  "texts": [
    "1 Accessible AI emphasizes usability specifically for people with disabilities (Morris 2020).",
    "However, distinctions between these terms are often relative, and they frequently overlap or are used interchangeably (Avellan, Sharma, and Turunen 2020).",
    "Clearly delineating \"AI for All\" remains a research gap.",
    "While some consensus has been achieved regarding \"AI for All\", little legislation to protect the idea, leaving to a kind of contradiction in status quo.",
    "Documents such as the Ethical Guidelines for Artificial Intelligence, the Global Digital Compact, and China's Ethical Norms for a New Generation of Artificial Intelligence have all included the notion of \"AI for All\" as a fundamental principle."
  ]
}